rows.project_objective:
The event targeted at the civil servants involved in the public service delivery in the countries of the Region. The round table came up with analyzing the current trends and achieved results among participating countries to increase the access to the public services and the quality of public service delivery in three dimensions: 
-	changes in normative legal acts;
-	changes in the public service delivery practice;
-	development of the public feedback system;

rows.ssc_description:
The initiatives for 2014 were set according to the findings of the Baseline study 2013 following initatives were specified based on the findings of the study: 
•	strategic state planning;
•	civil servants' performance appraisal;
•	anti-corruption policy (ethics and integrity);
•	e-government;
The round table covered most of the priority topics set for this year.

rows.project_objective:
Exchange experiences and learn how to make national REDD+ systems more robust and credible in order to attain benefits in the international arena;
Increase collaboration among the HFLD countries, creating a platform to discuss strategies to maximize benefits from REDD+ and strategies to form an unified block in negotiations;
Increase understanding of REDD+ as a tool for sustainable development; and
Maintain the existing national and international momentum for REDD+.
